body:
### Welcome to Farhatagwaeten Page.
This is the easiest way to see my beautiful pages that show all of my objective, Education,and Technical Skills.

### OBJECTIVE:
A proven software developer with more than 3 years of experience in software, web development, information technology industry field, and goal oriented to developing excellent quality products that meet all stakeholders’ needs. I am seeking a challenging opportunity to participate and contribute in building, and managing small or large software projects where my advanced skills, education, extensive training, and many years of experience can be fully utilized. 
___
### Education
**1. Master of Software Engineering.** 
 * Concordia University - Montréal, QC 
 * September 2011 - July 2014

**2. Bachelor of Computer Science.** 
 * Omar Al Mukhtar University, Derna branch, Libya.
 * October 2001 - July 2005

___

### Technical Skills. 

**1. Front-End technologies:**
   * HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, jQuery.

___

**2. Back-End technologies:** 
   * Java SE, Java EE, JSP, Servlet, PHP.) 
   * Data access: JDBC, Hibernate, Object Relational Mapping, and JPA.
   * Unit Testing: TDD Test Driven Development, Java unit testing with JUnit, framework.
   * Analysis the quality of code with (Sonar source, Logiscope, and McCabe).  
   * Relational Databases: SQL, MySQL, Oracle 10 and 11 g.
   * Web Services: SOAP, RESTful.
   * Development IDE Tools: Eclipse, NetBeans, JDeveloper, and Sublime text 3.
   * Software Application Server: XAMP, Apache Tomcat 7, Glassfish 4, and JBoss 7.1.
   * Code Version Control: Subversion, CVS, SVN, Bitbucket, Git and GitHub.
   * Development Methodology: Agile methodology (SCRUM Framework + Kanban).

___

**3. Software Development:** 
   * Eliciting Requirements (functional and non-functional), UML.
   * Software Architecture (4 +1 View Model), designs patterns.


### Support or Contact
Having trouble with Pages? Check out our [Facebook](https://facebook/farhatagwaeten) or [Twitter:](https://Twitter\farhatagwaeten) and I’ll get back to you shortly.
